# Vercel Deployment & Strict TypeScript

Projects deploying to Vercel must avoid implicit `any`. Follow these patterns.

## Callback Parameter Types

### Prisma `$transaction` callbacks

```typescript
await prisma.$transaction(async (tx: Parameters<Parameters<typeof prisma.$transaction>[0]>[0]) => { ... });
```

### Array `.map()` callbacks (Prisma results)

```typescript
return items.map((item: (typeof items)[number]) => ({ ... }));
// Or with type alias:
type ItemType = (typeof items)[number];
return items.map((item: ItemType) => ({ ... }));
```

## Pre-Deploy Checklist

1. Run `npm run build` before push.
2. Or `npm run build:clean` to match Vercel (no cache).
3. Or `npm run typecheck` for faster check (excludes tests).

## Package Manager

Use npm. Remove pnpm-lock.yaml if present.

## Next.js 16

`serverActions` under `experimental` in next.config.ts.
